geneVariantDescriptions.description: NPM1 amplification indicates an increased number of copies of the NPM1 gene. However, the mechanism causing the increase is unspecified.

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, anaplastic large cell lymphoma cell lines harboring an amplification of NPM1-ALK were resistant to Alunbrig (brigatinib) in culture (PMID: 25421750).

evidence.efficacyEvidence: In a preclinical study, anaplastic large cell lymphoma cell lines harboring an amplification of NPM1-ALK demonstrated a decreased response compared to parental cell lines harboring NPM1-ALK when treated with Alecensa (alectinib) in culture (PMID: 25421750).
